                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I spent a lot of time in HoH.  It's a great zone to polish up your charming skills.  Invis will get you just about anywhere in the zone (some mobs see invis but there are very few).  
<br />

<br />
If you take the path turning left at every opportunity will take you to a shrine entrance guarded with 3 wrulons.  When you see the cats, stop and look to your right, you should see another hall guarded with 2 hero shrine guardian.  Enter that hall and go straight to the back, that is a safe spot.
<br />

<br />
There are too few mobs nearby to keep a full group happy but for a chanter working his charming skills with a friend or 2, and eventually soloing, it is an ideal spot.  Inside that structure (including the hero shrine guardians), there are a total of 14 mobs.  3 pairs require pacification to split the first time around (I usually pull hero shrines guardian together since they are wussie.)  Anyway, just make your way there and experiment, eventually you will clear the whole structure solo and you should start feeling more comfortable with charm by then.
<br />

<br />
There you have it, have fun and let me know if it works for you <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
