                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">And while the faucet of good advice has been opened wide, here's my 2 bits : if your pet gets low on health, cast recant magic on it ( will strip 4 buffs so both charm and haste are gone) and nuke it down. After some practice you will get the feeling for timing and be able to nuke both ex-pet and it's latest victim for 5-6% aaxp instead of the 3-4% of a pet induced death. And get a blue ceramic band ( dirt cheap on bazaar or home made if you have some skill at pottery) to get some points of damage in on every kill. The Bcb is a great pulling tool too, since it only does 5 points of damage. If a tank so much as sneezes at an incoming mob he will take aggro.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=345084&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Anaximander </a>
<br />
of Lowland Elites
