                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">BTW - Opposite to what Nokei posted, if you are charming in BoT, get an elemental. They DON'T summon. Even at 50% health left, they will just run for you if charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
If you ARE charming something that summons, make sure the groups healer knows. In my regular group, the ranger takes over most of my pets management for me. He keep an eye on it. When charm breaks, he immediately snares it and kites while I recharm. He also announces to the healer when and if to heal my pet. He makes my life so much easier.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=750403" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="color: red"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Arcady</span></span></a>
<br />
