                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">This isn't recomended for everyone, but if you've got fast hands, decent gear and spell haste, it's sometimes better NOT to stand far away from the pet.  That might sound counter intuitive, but if you can time a recast of WoM or Color Cloud just right, you can manage your pet all by yourself.  Add to this Mesmerization Mastery, and you can WoM, hit a hot key asking the shaman/mage to remalo the pet, tash and recharm all before WoM wears off.
<br />

<br />
This is what works best for me, and it even works out ok in GoD.  Keep in mind I'm fairly well geared.  But it's mostly a matter of timing, and I've got it down so close that even when the broken pet stuns me, I can cast PBAE between rounds and catch him.  I often have both WoM and Color Cloud up just in case.
<br />

<br />
Get mez mastery!  Whether you're a straight crowd control enchanter or a regular charmer, you'll not regret any of those 20 AAs <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=515779" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://lunapark.org/~luna/mithrasig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
